# lonloop.com — Cloudflare Pages redirect/rewrite rules.
# Syntax: <from> <to> <status>. Status 200 = rewrite (URL stays put, other
# content is served); anything 3xx would be a visible redirect.

# The World Monitor mirror is built for "/" but served from "/worldmonitor/".
# scripts/worldmonitor/build.sh passes --base=/worldmonitor/, which fixes the
# paths Vite emits but not the ones the app bakes in as root-absolute string
# literals: map data, notification icons, map styles, globe textures. Left
# alone they match no static asset, fall through to the SPA fallback and come
# back as 200 text/html — the map layer's JSON parse throws and everything else
# fails silently. Each prefix below exists under /worldmonitor/ and is
# referenced nowhere else on this site, so bending the whole prefix is safe.
#
# Deliberately absent: /assets/ shows up in the bundles only inside a
# t.includes("/assets/") URL classifier, never as a fetch target; /api/ is a
# real route served by functions/api/[[path]].js; /home/, /buy/, /docs/ and
# /embed/ are upstream SPA routes with no local counterpart.
/data/*        /worldmonitor/data/:splat        200
/favico/*      /worldmonitor/favico/:splat      200
/map-styles/*  /worldmonitor/map-styles/:splat  200
/textures/*    /worldmonitor/textures/:splat    200
